##DC miscellany | rounded up for another week

Micro signal

Features are presented, some fairly limited thoughts and memories.

Close buildings informed me yesterday that they would reopen at any time. Recently, I receive news from the Internet every day. I can only see a small square of road from my window. Although the traffic is still very heavy, I still run every evening, walk my dog, walk my baby, but it feels very close. It's been almost a week now, so let's take this opportunity to get rid of the stuff you left at school and take a look at the outside world.
(long-term hand remnant eye, photography level is on the verge of fusing

Pick-up / delivery only signs were posted in familiar shops along the way, chairs were either removed or upended, and some favourite eateries were closed, as if a year had passed. Originally a white (not really) pear has grown out of the leaves, a distant view of a green light. Fortunately, the Cherry Blossoms and Magnolia denudata had been connected, and it was spring and clear. It makes people sigh with emotion red like fire, pink like Chardonnay, white like snow, relaxed and happy, love and disgrace together forget, put the wine on the wind, its joy is foreign.

The Cherry Blossoms in front of the building seem to open overnight, and it seems not to be. The once bustling building has been deserted, no one, only the security uncle and cleaning aunt is still maintaining the operation of the empty building. Time was long before I met her, but is longer since we parted,.

After picking up my things, I began to wander. Suddenly, if there is no epidemic, DC spring is very suitable for young lovers to fall in love. I've got to keep my hands to myself, or I'M GONNA end up with a candy bar.
(take, for example, the rollercoaster ride below, in which a woman doesn't even recognize her mother if she doesn't take care of the candy.)

I don't remember seeing a lot of cherry blossoms. In Shanghai for so many years, because of fear of people, so never go to Gu village or Tongji ran over busy. Although Jiaotong University has cherry blossoms, but I have never found Cherry blossom cards are scattered, the United States is beautiful, difficult into the climate. Today, before I reached the Tidal Basin, I saw a circle of Cherry blossoms by the lake in the distance. It's not yet in full bloom, but it's a rare sight. But it was the old master who was unfriendly. Oh No, the old master was friendly. The old master was unfriendly. It's not a lot of people coming and going, but it's a narrow road, especially during the outbreak, and I don't care if it's a big head, it's a big head.
Btw, I suggest you bring your sister. You can still get there when no one's on the road, but it's pretty hard. And it's not like Asia, where every now and then you get a pretty sister in the shot, here may be the reflection of the black brother (and these Columbia like to wear dark clothes, you pull this later, the trunk changes, the face changes... otherwise you pull the trunk, the clothes change, the face change... anyway...)
I recorded some footage on my way back, and I made a video of everything that's been going on lately, so just watch.

In fact, everything in the home is not short of, but out of want to toss about some other, still went to the supermarket to reach a bit. As a result, I can only say that the above "Jue" said too early, this supermarket is really jue.
Nearly 90 percent of the vegetables were sold, the meat shelves were mostly empty, and there was only a small amount of water left in the VATS. There was no toilet paper stored around the world, no Napkins, no hand sanitizer, no sanitisers? There's not much cereal left, there's not much tea left, we're out of flour (I should check the salt stores) , my baby wants to buy Tofu and honey ？? Observed under the staff in the replenishment of goods, found sufficient supply of honey juice has fruit, eggs, milk, wine, kitchen paper? (Come on. They are not substitute!) And the difference between restocking and out-of-stock cabbages (suddenly all the supermarkets have so many cabbages, I wonder if They've moved the stock? ? ?) It's a vivid illustration of the eight characters "death in a drought, death in a flood. " (as for why this is the only illustration for this time, because I think that touching the goods and touching the mobile phone is too much, so sleep well.)
Adhering to the idea of going out for once and then walking a bit more and taking a closer look at the social situation, I then went to the three small supermarkets near my home, but two told me they were sold out, one told me they don't sell Tofu. Although Americans may not be a large demand for Tofu so the supply will not be much, but! ! Isn't that amazing? Is it that hard to buy Tofu ？！? It means I could kill myself for a piece of Tofu ？？? This is really good for me ？? But I find that the stock is restocked at noon here, so friends may as well go shopping later in the afternoon / evening.
And seriously, the only thing I saw on the road today was a big black brother wearing a mask with his nose out, and the first time I saw a big white sister wearing a mask at Harris Teeter, no one else was doing what they were supposed to be doing. Brave, brilliant. While masts and oars vanished to flying ash and smoke. Guys, guys, guys, guys, guys, you really don't think there's a contradiction in terms.
Sure enough, once we got home, it melted again. Fine:)
Afternoon people sitting at home, mail heaven, the rest of the class, online classes are all contracted. Fine:)
You can't help who you are. Friends, take care of yourself and try to be happy. Looking forward to our next long-lost Reunion.
